# === Role-based artifact policy (see CLAUDE.md "Experiment Artifacts: Tracked vs Ignored") ===
#
# `_artifacts/` mirrors `results/` and holds bulk reproducible outputs (.eqx
# checkpoints, training logs, large arrays, full-DPI figure renders). Nothing inside
# is tracked. The directory is shared across worktrees via `.worktree.yaml` (see
# Bug: 0887e3e) — `wt` symlinks `_artifacts` from the main worktree into every
# feature worktree at creation time, so all worktrees write to the same location.
# The pattern is written without a trailing slash so it also matches the symlink
# itself (a symlink is not a directory from git's perspective). For the symlink to
# be created cleanly at worktree creation, no files under `_artifacts/` may be
# tracked (a tracked file would be materialized by `git checkout` and conflict
# with the symlink replacement that `wt` performs).
_artifacts
#
# Inside `results/`, ignore everything by default and whitelist specific kinds.
# This makes tracking depend on the file's ROLE (spec/narrative/render-thumbnail),
# not on the directory's NAME. New cloud providers (runpod/, modal/, etc.) and new
# experiment phases never need a new ignore line.
results/**
# Keep directory structure traversable so nested whitelists apply:
!results/**/
# Narratives (long-form analyses, READMEs, per-run notes):
!results/**/*.md
# Run specs (canonical: run.json; legacy: config.json):
!results/**/run.json
# config.json whitelisted at specific depths only — intentionally NOT `!results/**/config.json`.
# The broad glob is depth-blind and would track bulk per-run configs from cloud providers
# (runpod/, modal/, coreweave/, etc.) that land deep in the tree. Restrict to the three
# legacy layouts that actually exist:
#   depth 2: results/<exp>/config.json
#   depth 3: results/<exp>/<subdir>/config.json  (e.g. running_cost_nn1e6/)
#   depth 4 via models/: results/<exp>/models/<run>/config.json
# If you find yourself wanting to add a new depth or path here, the config.json is probably
# a bulk artifact — put it under _artifacts/ and use run.json for the spec.
!results/*/config.json
!results/*/*/config.json
!results/*/models/*/config.json
# Figure / analysis specs (always committed, see threshold rule for renders):
!results/**/spec.json
# Small Plotly figure JSON (commit only when ≤ 2 MB; enforced by the saver helper):
!results/**/figure.json
# Typora-style markdown sidecar assets (results/<name>.assets/*.png) — keep tracked:
!results/**/*.assets/**
# Figure thumbnails (commit only when ≤ 300 KB at 100 DPI; enforced by the saver helper):
!results/**/figures/**/figure.png
# Render symlinks (relative symlink from results/<exp>/figures/<topic>/ → _artifacts/...; Bug: aaafc55):
!results/**/figures/**/figure.html
# Empty-directory markers (rare; useful for placeholders):
!results/**/.gitkeep
# Experiment-specific Python scripts (per CLAUDE.md "Script placement", Bug: 8404108).
# Only under results/<exp>/scripts/ — keeps the whitelist tight so bulk .py files
# elsewhere under results/ (e.g. accidentally-saved repls) don't get tracked.
!results/**/scripts/*.py
# Note: bulk artifacts (.eqx, large .npz, .log, full-DPI renders, runpod/, modal/, etc.)
# are NOT whitelisted above, so they fall through to the ignore. They belong under _artifacts/.
